LLM-only navigation layer over the codebase. Wiki pages cite code regions directly — no intermediate design-doc layer. This file is the master schema for the `{{DOMAIN}}` wiki; it is self-contained.

## 3-layer LLM-only architecture

- **L0 — Source-of-truth.** Code + ADRs + linked docs under the source repos. Never duplicated; only cited.
- **L1 — Routing manifest.** `{{DOMAIN}}/retrieval.yaml`. Deterministic task-pattern → file-path map. Read FIRST by `/wiki-query`, `/wiki-ingest`, `/wiki-lint`.
- **L2 — Atomic insight pages.** `{{DOMAIN}}/pages/*.md`. Each page must justify itself on at least one of: gotcha / invariant / why-non-obvious / observed-failure-mode. Target ~80–150 words.
- **L3 — Decay tracker.** Per-source `cited_region` + `content_hash` in frontmatter. `/wiki-lint` re-hashes on demand and flags drift. Per-repo `sync:` SHA in `.last-sync` + `retrieval.yaml` anchors staleness.

